<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-013-180  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 013 180.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Dec 25 1989 v6 n51 p2(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users angry as FCC extends LECs' 12% rate of return. (localexchange carriers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Runnoe, Gail.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The FCC decides to extend its current 12 percent rate of returncap for local exchange carriers, including Bell regional holdingcompanies.andP;  MCI Communications Corp, the Consumer Federation ofAmerica and the International Communications Associations want theFCC to lower the cap to 10.4 percent to reflect current marketconditions.andP;  They claim the lower rate of return will saveconsumers $400 million a year on switched and special accessservices.andP;  The FCC wants to investigate further in preparation forimplementing price caps in the fall of 1990.andP;  The consumer groupsfeel the FCC's decision is a sign that the new commission will beas ineffectual in safeguarding consumer interests as the previouscommission.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionPricing PolicyTelephone Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>